solution: We have $3 \text{ ft} = 1 \text{ yd}$. Cubing both sides, we get $27 \text{ ft}^3 = 1 \text{ yd}^3$. So there are $\boxed{27}$ cubic feet in one cubic yard.
model_solution:
1 cubic yard is equal to $3\times 3\times 3=27$ cubic feet.
Since we are looking for how many cubic feet are in one cubic yard, we need to divide the amount of cubic feet in one cubic yard by one.
The next step is: $\frac{27}{1}$.
$\frac{27}{1}=27$
$\frac{27}{1}=27$
